Collection --> represent the group of element/object /data into single entity.
Collection framework --> group of Interfaces, classes and algorithms

  Requirement                   |           Best collection usage
1.  Fast search by Index                        ArrayList
2.  Frequent Insert/Delete                      LinkedList
3.  Unique elements                                 Set
4.  Key-value storage                               Map
5.  FIFO processing                                Queue


LinkedList:
    ---> Each element is node
    ---> Each node contains 1. Data
                            2. Address of previous element
                            3. Address of Next element

Queue:
    ---> used to store elements in FIFO(first in first out) order. eg: task scheduler, buffering etc..
Methods in Queue:
    Insert      add()/offer()
    Delete      remove()/poll()
    Examine     element()/peek()

DeQueue:
    ---> also known as 'Deck'(pronounciation) , Double-ended Queue
    --> linear data structure , allows insertion and deletion of elements from both ends(head and tail)
    --> genralization of both FIFO(Queue) and LIFO(stack)

Feature     |       Queue       |       Deque       |       Stack
Insertion         Tail only           Both ends          Top only
Removal           Head only           Both ends          Top only
Access            Head only           Both ends          Top only
Principle          FIFO             Both FIFO & LIFO        LIFO

Characteristics:
1. Bidirectional
2. No capacity restriction(except arrayblockingQueue)
3. No-Index based approach (like Queue,no get(index) method)
4. Null elements are not allowed(exception is linkedlist, preference is not to use)
5. O(1) -- All insertion and deletion at both ends are constant time

DeQue(Interface) ---> Implementation ---> LinkedList (class) , pointer(next,previous), more memory
                          |
                          ---> ArrayDeque (class) --> Resizeable array implementation, no pointers, less memory
Methods in Deque:
    Insert      addFirst(),addLast()/offerFirst(),offerLast()
    Delete      removeFirst(),removeLast()/pollFirst(),pollLast()
    Examine     getFirst(),getLast()/peekFirst(),peekLast()

    Stack       Push/Pop



