PriorityQueue:
    -->process bases on the priority instead of insertion order

Queue                           PriorityQueue
FIFO                               Priority Based
Insertion Order                    priority Based
use Linkedlist/ArrList             use Binary Heap(tree based data structure-MinHeap,MaxHeap)
First Inserted Removed             Highest/lowest priority removed


Set:
    --> collection that cannot contains duplicate elements[MUST contains unique elements]
    -->eg: passport number, Aadhar, PAN, Vehicle ID...
    --> models the mathematical set abstraction
Characteristics:
1. No Duplicates
2. No Index access
3. Unordered
4. Allow NULL value
5. Hashcode() and equal()/comparable()

Hashset:
    --> Most common implemenation of set interface
    --> It is backed by HashMap internally

Internal Working:
    --> HashMap created Key:Value pair combination and a dummy object value "PRESENT"(final variable)
    --> Key is the object added via Hashset eg: Apple, Banana etcc
    --> Uses Hashcode() and equal() to determine uniqueness
    --> Elements are stored in hash buckets--insertion order depends on hash code, not Inserstion order
when to use hashset:
1. fast lookup ,insert, delete object
2. union/intersection related mathematical model

Two terms on object creation(parameter)
1. Capacity :- default Capacity of HashSet : 16
2. Load factor :- when to create new hashset space : default :0.75 ~ 75%